251
00:15:19,920 --> 00:15:21,433
They'll be asking all kinds of questions.

252
00:15:21,433 --> 00:15:22,559
I don't know.

253
00:15:22,559 --> 00:15:26,679
How am I supposed to resist showing off
that you're my girlfriend?

254
00:15:27,468 --> 00:15:31,257
But at work,
our relationship stays strictly a secret. Okay?

255
00:15:31,257 --> 00:15:33,245
If we ever run into each other there,

256
00:15:33,245 --> 00:15:35,927
be careful.

257
00:15:35,927 --> 00:15:37,241
Why should I?

258
00:15:37,241 --> 00:15:38,416
Come on.

259
00:15:38,416 --> 00:15:40,055
You remember that video of us in the lobby

260
00:15:40,055 --> 00:15:42,346
being called the "public nuisance couple?"

261
00:15:42,346 --> 00:15:44,506
Word spreads crazy fast at the company.

262
00:15:44,506 --> 00:15:47,876
If rumors start flying again,
it'll just cause a headache.

263
00:15:47,876 --> 00:15:50,266
You don't have some other reason, do you?

264
00:15:50,266 --> 00:15:52,423
You know...

265
00:15:52,423 --> 00:15:54,141
him.

266
00:15:54,141 --> 00:15:55,801
Your first love.

267
00:15:55,801 --> 00:15:57,094
What?

268
00:15:57,094 --> 00:15:59,900
Are you jealous right now?

269
00:15:59,900 --> 00:16:01,857
Jealous? No.

270
00:16:01,857 --> 00:16:06,528
I'm just asking as your boyfriend.

271
00:16:06,528 --> 00:16:09,314
So we have to be careful at the villa,

272
00:16:09,314 --> 00:16:11,984
and keep it secret at work too...

273
00:16:11,984 --> 00:16:15,029
That means nothing's really changed
from before we started dating.

274
00:16:15,029 --> 00:16:17,264
What are you talking about?

275
00:16:17,264 --> 00:16:18,659
We're dating now.

276
00:16:18,659 --> 00:16:20,701
How is that the same?

277
00:16:20,701 --> 00:16:23,444
It's totally different.

278
00:16:24,573 --> 00:16:25,890
How is it different?

279
00:16:27,132 --> 00:16:31,737
Well, unless you actually show me
how it's different,

280
00:16:31,737 --> 00:16:34,596
I won't be convinced.

281
00:16:36,212 --> 00:16:39,712
Why are you being embarrassing like that?

282
00:16:40,637 --> 00:16:42,264
Hey.

283
00:16:42,264 --> 00:16:44,124
Embarrassing?

284
00:16:44,124 --> 00:16:46,758
We're a couple.

285
00:16:46,758 --> 00:16:50,738
Forget it. I knew you wouldn't do it anyway.

286
00:16:53,582 --> 00:16:54,856
How was that?

287
00:16:54,856 --> 00:16:57,726
Does it feel different now?

288
00:16:57,726 --> 00:16:59,506
Yeah.

289
00:16:59,506 --> 00:17:00,969
Totally different.

290
00:17:00,969 --> 00:17:02,951
But I'm still not completely sure.

291
00:17:02,951 --> 00:17:05,370
What I mean is... do it one more time.

292
00:17:05,370 --> 00:17:07,275
- One more time?
- Yeah.

293
00:17:07,275 --> 00:17:10,068
I'm ready.

294
00:17:22,364 --> 00:17:25,684
Woo Joo, did you poop?

295
00:17:30,946 --> 00:17:33,533
Of all times...

296
00:17:34,237 --> 00:17:38,068
- That smell.
- You can't sit like that.

297
00:17:40,698 --> 00:17:41,959
Woo Joo,

298
00:17:41,959 --> 00:17:44,004
Uncle has to go home now.

299
00:17:44,004 --> 00:17:45,702
No.

300
00:17:45,702 --> 00:17:47,348
Woo Joo, I'll come back tomorrow.

301
00:17:47,348 --> 00:17:48,705
I'll pick you up

302
00:17:48,705 --> 00:17:50,999
from daycare tomorrow, okay?

303
00:17:50,999 --> 00:17:53,598
Don't go.

304
00:17:56,262 --> 00:17:57,465
This isn't working.

305
00:17:57,465 --> 00:17:58,890
Let's take him for a quick walk
around the block.

306
00:17:58,890 --> 00:18:01,269
Woo Joo, come here.

307
00:18:02,386 --> 00:18:05,305
We've already gone around five times.

308
00:18:05,305 --> 00:18:08,934
I guess he was happy
having his uncle around at home again.

309
00:18:08,934 --> 00:18:11,097
Yeah.

310
00:18:12,186 --> 00:18:13,188
Hyun Jin.

311
00:18:13,188 --> 00:18:14,481
Yeah?

312
00:18:14,481 --> 00:18:17,435
I've been thinking...

313
00:18:18,652 --> 00:18:21,279
Maybe we should

314
00:18:21,279 --> 00:18:24,402
live together again.

315
00:18:26,368 --> 00:18:28,120
If I keep going back and forth like this,

316
00:18:28,120 --> 00:18:30,580
Woo Joo might feel uneasy.

317
00:18:30,580 --> 00:18:31,915
And if I'm living there,

318
00:18:31,915 --> 00:18:35,902
you wouldn't have to leave him
with grandma all the time.

319
00:18:37,212 --> 00:18:38,797
After all,

320
00:18:38,797 --> 00:18:42,765
it's best for him
to have a guardian by his side.

321
00:18:43,531 --> 00:18:47,689
You don't have to answer right now.
Just think about it.

322
00:18:49,516 --> 00:18:51,643
I'm in.

323
00:18:51,643 --> 00:18:53,770
Really?

324
00:18:53,770 --> 00:18:55,543
You can take more time to think it over.

325
00:18:55,543 --> 00:18:57,983
What's there to think about?

326
00:18:57,983 --> 00:18:59,776
Woo Joo's the real owner of that house.

327
00:18:59,776 --> 00:19:02,696
And I bet he'd love having you move in.

328
00:19:02,696 --> 00:19:03,989
- Really?
- Yeah.

329
00:19:03,989 --> 00:19:06,241
I should ask him.

330
00:19:06,241 --> 00:19:07,909
Don't wake him.

331
00:19:07,909 --> 00:19:10,298
Just go home and start packing.

332
00:19:10,298 --> 00:19:11,371
But

333
00:19:11,371 --> 00:19:12,984
if you move in this time,

334
00:19:12,984 --> 00:19:16,543
you can't just leave whenever you want.

335
00:19:16,543 --> 00:19:17,711
Of course.

336
00:19:17,711 --> 00:19:19,254
Even if you tell me to leave,

337
00:19:19,254 --> 00:19:20,642
I'm not going anywhere.

338
00:19:20,642 --> 00:19:23,476
- Really?
- Yeah.

339
00:19:23,476 --> 00:19:25,109
Go pack your things.

340
00:19:25,109 --> 00:19:27,033
- When are you moving in?
- Right now.

341
00:19:27,033 --> 00:19:28,447
Right now!

342
00:19:28,447 --> 00:19:29,895
Yeah?

343
00:19:29,895 --> 00:19:32,480
Thank you.

344
00:19:39,692 --> 00:19:42,236
But does this situation even make sense?

345
00:19:42,236 --> 00:19:44,071
He's supposed to be in the U.S.,

346
00:19:44,071 --> 00:19:47,025
so why is he at today's meeting?

347
00:19:47,025 --> 00:19:49,869
I was just too worried about Filmpluto.

348
00:19:49,869 --> 00:19:51,878
I couldn't bring myself to leave.

349
00:19:51,878 --> 00:19:53,242
That's odd.

350
00:19:53,242 --> 00:19:56,834
Everything seemed perfectly fine without you.

351
00:19:56,834 --> 00:19:58,314
Good work today.

352
00:19:58,314 --> 00:20:00,421
Manager Jo, you did a good job.

353
00:20:00,421 --> 00:20:02,757
Come on, it was nothing.

354
00:20:02,757 --> 00:20:05,016
Anyway, we're heading out to eat,

355
00:20:05,016 --> 00:20:06,890
so you guys can clock out whenever.

356
00:20:06,890 --> 00:20:07,921
Yes.

357
00:20:07,921 --> 00:20:09,096
What should we eat?

358
00:20:09,096 --> 00:20:12,308
Want to go to that brunch place you like?

359
00:20:12,308 --> 00:20:14,060
Let's get sundae soup.

360
00:20:14,060 --> 00:20:15,436
Sundae soup?

361
00:20:15,436 --> 00:20:16,979
You can't even eat that.

362
00:20:16,979 --> 00:20:19,246
You like it, so let's go.

363
00:20:20,858 --> 00:20:23,984
Hurry up. I'm starving.

364
00:20:24,584 --> 00:20:26,572
You didn't have to go that far for me.

365
00:20:26,572 --> 00:20:29,623
Wait, Choo.

366
00:20:29,623 --> 00:20:31,765
Choo!

367
00:20:33,579 --> 00:20:34,872
Seriously?

368
00:20:34,872 --> 00:20:37,430
There's no middle ground with them.

369
00:20:37,430 --> 00:20:38,466
He said he'd quit...

370
00:20:38,466 --> 00:20:42,720
I just finished my meeting.

371
00:20:42,720 --> 00:20:45,849
Looks like I might get off early today.

372
00:20:45,849 --> 00:20:47,301
So annoying.

373
00:20:47,301 --> 00:20:49,679
This work environment is the worst.

374
00:20:49,679 --> 00:20:52,014
Why isn't she reading it?

375
00:20:52,014 --> 00:20:53,641
Lucky you.

376
00:20:53,641 --> 00:20:54,910
I've got a meeting soon.

377
00:20:54,910 --> 00:20:57,356
I'll text you later.

378
00:21:03,107 --> 00:21:05,393
[Deer class]

379
00:21:05,393 --> 00:21:08,533
Come over here.

380
00:21:11,805 --> 00:21:13,432
Woo Joo,

381
00:21:13,432 --> 00:21:16,300
how about letting Na Yeon have one of the toys?

382
00:21:16,300 --> 00:21:17,338
Woo Joo,

383
00:21:17,338 --> 00:21:21,106
toys are meant to be shared with your friends.

384
00:21:21,106 --> 00:21:22,774
Okay? Just one.

385
00:21:22,774 --> 00:21:24,026
No.

386
00:21:24,026 --> 00:21:27,410
We share our toys with our friends, okay?

387
00:21:30,282 --> 00:21:31,641
Woo Joo, let's go.

388
00:21:31,641 --> 00:21:33,118
Hold my hand.

389
00:21:33,118 --> 00:21:35,704
Excuse me, sir.

390
00:21:35,704 --> 00:21:39,924
Do you have a moment?

391
00:21:45,158 --> 00:21:48,593
Sorry, but I have a girlfriend.

392
00:21:51,360 --> 00:21:53,859
Oh, I see...

393
00:21:55,098 --> 00:21:58,471
[Saetbyeol Daycare]
Woo Joo, let's step outside for a moment.

394
00:22:06,151 --> 00:22:08,695
Well...

395
00:22:08,695 --> 00:22:12,032
Is there something wrong with Woo Joo?

396
00:22:12,032 --> 00:22:14,499
Nothing serious.

397
00:22:14,499 --> 00:22:15,522
That's a relief.

398
00:22:15,522 --> 00:22:17,815
Lately at home, has he been saying things like

399
00:22:17,815 --> 00:22:18,983
"No" or "I don't want to"

400
00:22:18,983 --> 00:22:21,650
more often?

401
00:22:21,650 --> 00:22:22,959
No.

402
00:22:22,959 --> 00:22:25,045
No.

403
00:22:25,045 --> 00:22:26,630
No.

404
00:22:26,630 --> 00:22:27,923
Right.

405
00:22:27,923 --> 00:22:29,925
Lately he's been talking a lot more,

406
00:22:29,925 --> 00:22:34,763
but whenever we ask him to do something,
he just says no and won't listen.

407
00:22:34,763 --> 00:22:37,460
Teacher, is this serious?

408
00:22:37,460 --> 00:22:38,520
No.

409
00:22:38,520 --> 00:22:39,726
[Our Child Has Changed]

410
00:22:39,726 --> 00:22:40,522
No.

411
00:22:40,522 --> 00:22:41,798
As children grow,

412
00:22:41,798 --> 00:22:44,564
they start to develop their own opinions
and a sense of independence.

413
00:22:44,564 --> 00:22:46,274
It's a very natural phase.

414
00:22:46,274 --> 00:22:47,901
Sometimes they want something,

415
00:22:47,901 --> 00:22:49,721
but since their language skills
are still developing,

416
00:22:49,721 --> 00:22:51,172
they just say "no" instead.

417
00:22:53,239 --> 00:22:56,393
At times like this,
instead of giving in to everything,

418
00:22:56,393 --> 00:22:59,746
it's better to clearly explain
what is and isn't allowed.

419
00:22:59,746 --> 00:23:01,456
You can offer them other options,

420
00:23:01,456 --> 00:23:05,585
or help them learn to wait.

421
00:23:05,585 --> 00:23:08,088
Other options... and learning to wait.

422
00:23:08,088 --> 00:23:09,673
Having consistent rules

423
00:23:09,673 --> 00:23:11,216
actually helps children

424
00:23:11,216 --> 00:23:14,028
feel more emotionally secure.

425
00:23:19,906 --> 00:23:21,726
The ball rolled over there.

426
00:23:21,726 --> 00:23:22,755
Be careful.

427
00:23:22,755 --> 00:23:25,161
There's no way my kid has
that "I-don't-want-to" phase.

428
00:23:25,161 --> 00:23:28,477
Don't worry.
He's playing just fine. He'll be okay.

429
00:23:28,477 --> 00:23:29,512
Right.

430
00:23:29,512 --> 00:23:31,862
You know what they say
about the "terrible two years."

431
00:23:31,862 --> 00:23:34,281
Yeo Reum was a handful at that age too.

432
00:23:34,281 --> 00:23:35,474
By the way,

433
00:23:35,474 --> 00:23:38,187
I saw you carrying
a bunch of stuff inside earlier.

434
00:23:38,187 --> 00:23:39,236
What's going on?

435
00:23:39,236 --> 00:23:42,456
So you two are living together again?

436
00:23:42,456 --> 00:23:44,774
Well... yeah.

437
00:23:44,774 --> 00:23:45,859
Right.

438
00:23:48,489 --> 00:23:50,714
Back when you spilled all that meat
at the camping trip,

439
00:23:50,714 --> 00:23:53,049
I thought you two really didn't get along.

440
00:23:53,049 --> 00:23:54,843
See? You never know with couples.

441
00:23:54,843 --> 00:23:56,386
Exactly.

442
00:23:56,386 --> 00:23:58,805
Then who was that guy who came to the recital?

443
00:23:58,805 --> 00:24:00,932
I thought he was Hyun Jin's boyfriend.

444
00:24:00,932 --> 00:24:02,225
A guy? Who?

445
00:24:02,225 --> 00:24:06,229
You know,
that really tall, super handsome guy was there.

446
00:24:06,229 --> 00:24:08,023
Maybe your eyesight's not so great.

447
00:24:08,023 --> 00:24:10,965
Not that handsome.

448
00:24:10,965 --> 00:24:12,360
Why?

449
00:24:12,360 --> 00:24:16,309
How about taking a trip with Woo Joo?

450
00:24:16,309 --> 00:24:17,363
A trip?

451
00:24:17,363 --> 00:24:20,785
Kids that age have so much energy.

452
00:24:20,785 --> 00:24:22,245
If they stay home all the time,

453
00:24:22,245 --> 00:24:23,788
they get restless and stop listening.

454
00:24:23,788 --> 00:24:25,026
But if you go somewhere nice,

455
00:24:25,026 --> 00:24:26,208
let them see nature

456
00:24:26,208 --> 00:24:28,108
and do outdoor activities, it really helps.

457
00:24:28,108 --> 00:24:30,170
That's why we started camping.

458
00:24:30,170 --> 00:24:31,755
Oh, a trip.

459
00:24:31,755 --> 00:24:34,132
Yeah, a trip sounds good.

460
00:24:34,132 --> 00:24:36,130
Now that you two are officially back together,

461
00:24:36,130 --> 00:24:37,469
go spend time together.

462
00:24:37,469 --> 00:24:38,845
And while you're at it,

463
00:24:38,845 --> 00:24:40,555
shout to the whole world,

464
00:24:40,555 --> 00:24:43,391
"My girlfriend is this adorable!"

465
00:24:43,391 --> 00:24:46,191
Go do whatever you've been wanting to do.

466
00:24:46,191 --> 00:24:48,441
That's cringey.

467
00:24:50,815 --> 00:24:53,721
Go play.

468
00:25:03,287 --> 00:25:05,747
[The Family Investigation Office]
[Seoul Family Court]

469
00:25:05,747 --> 00:25:09,680
The Family Investigation Office
at the Seoul Family Court?

470
00:25:11,044 --> 00:25:14,631
It's addressed to Hyun Jin.

471
00:25:14,631 --> 00:25:16,007
What is this?

472
00:25:16,007 --> 00:25:18,176
Hey, Uncle.

473
00:25:18,176 --> 00:25:19,636
Woo Joo, what is it?

474
00:25:19,636 --> 00:25:21,388
Want to play cars?

475
00:25:21,388 --> 00:25:23,598
Yeah.

476
00:25:23,598 --> 00:25:25,795
Run!

477
00:25:25,795 --> 00:25:27,352
Run, run.

478
00:25:27,352 --> 00:25:28,728
Run, run!

479
00:25:28,728 --> 00:25:30,146
Run!

480
00:25:30,146 --> 00:25:31,231
Starting this week,

481
00:25:31,231 --> 00:25:33,650
we'll begin selling
the tteokbokki meal kits offline,

482
00:25:33,650 --> 00:25:35,318
so please keep checking

483
00:25:35,318 --> 00:25:36,987
to make sure there are no supply issues.

484
00:25:36,987 --> 00:25:38,054
Got it.

485
00:25:38,054 --> 00:25:40,365
Manager, by the way,

486
00:25:40,365 --> 00:25:42,271
are we participating in the overseas expo?

487
00:25:42,271 --> 00:25:44,494
It just seems like

488
00:25:44,494 --> 00:25:46,413
a bit much for our team.

489
00:25:46,413 --> 00:25:49,332
The GloMarket project wrapped up successfully,

490
00:25:49,332 --> 00:25:51,001
so I thought this would be
a good time to push for it.

491
00:25:51,001 --> 00:25:53,128
You all already have a lot on your plates,

492
00:25:53,128 --> 00:25:55,630
so I don't want to put this on you too.

493
00:25:55,630 --> 00:25:57,048
This time,

494
00:25:57,048 --> 00:25:59,963
I'll handle it myself.

495
00:26:12,032 --> 00:26:15,084
Good evening. Dinner's ready.

496
00:26:16,261 --> 00:26:17,425
Hey, you scared me.

497
00:26:17,425 --> 00:26:20,818
Woo Joo, come here.

498
00:26:27,537 --> 00:26:29,123
Now it finally feels like our home.

499
00:26:29,123 --> 00:26:30,665
It's felt pretty empty without you.

500
00:26:30,665 --> 00:26:32,417
I'm sticking right here from now on.

501
00:26:32,417 --> 00:26:35,457
I'm not going anywhere.

502
00:26:36,379 --> 00:26:38,173
But is that all your stuff?

503
00:26:38,173 --> 00:26:39,716
That's not much.

504
00:26:39,716 --> 00:26:41,760
I just brought the essentials for now.

505
00:26:41,760 --> 00:26:44,553
I'll bring the rest little by little.

506
00:26:46,549 --> 00:26:48,753
If there's anything you need
from the furniture I have,

507
00:26:48,753 --> 00:26:50,393
take a look before I get rid of it.

508
00:26:50,393 --> 00:26:53,021
Okay.

509
00:26:53,021 --> 00:26:54,717
Where's my phone?

510
00:26:54,717 --> 00:26:55,732
What?

511
00:26:55,732 --> 00:26:57,364
Did you drop it somewhere?

512
00:26:57,364 --> 00:26:58,860
No.

513
00:26:58,860 --> 00:27:00,333
Call it for me.

514
00:27:00,333 --> 00:27:02,155
Okay.

515
00:27:02,155 --> 00:27:05,588
Woo Joo, have you seen my phone?

516
00:27:10,413 --> 00:27:13,046
Oh, here it is.

517
00:27:13,046 --> 00:27:14,070
Oh, thank you.

518
00:27:14,070 --> 00:27:14,862
[Temporary Housing]

519
00:27:14,862 --> 00:27:16,753
What? "Temporary Housing?"

520
00:27:16,753 --> 00:27:19,714
You saved your girlfriend
as "Temporary Housing?"

521
00:27:19,714 --> 00:27:22,800
No, that's not it.

522
00:27:22,800 --> 00:27:26,366
I saved that a long time ago.

523
00:27:27,421 --> 00:27:29,224
Then what did you save me as?

524
00:27:30,211 --> 00:27:31,810
- Well...
- Let me see. Don't hide it.

525
00:27:31,810 --> 00:27:32,811
No, it's just... something.

526
00:27:32,811 --> 00:27:34,145
You saved me as "Something?"

527
00:27:34,145 --> 00:27:35,355
- No!
- What is it then?

528
00:27:35,355 --> 00:27:38,481
I told you, it's just something.

529
00:28:01,316 --> 00:28:03,133
- Woo Joo.
- Hey.

530
00:28:03,133 --> 00:28:05,538
When did you get here?

531
00:28:05,538 --> 00:28:08,167
How long have you been there?

532
00:28:11,558 --> 00:28:14,298
I think he saw us.

533
00:28:26,225 --> 00:28:28,450
Are you keeping an eye on us?

534
00:28:28,450 --> 00:28:31,668
We can't do anything with him around.

535
00:28:31,668 --> 00:28:34,240
I guess we'll have to be careful

536
00:28:34,240 --> 00:28:36,846
when Woo Joo's awake.

537
00:28:38,084 --> 00:28:40,069
So when he's asleep,

538
00:28:40,069 --> 00:28:42,220
we can do whatever we want?

539
00:28:42,220 --> 00:28:43,506
What are you talking about?

540
00:28:43,506 --> 00:28:44,994
You shouldn't say things like that
in front of a kid.

541
00:28:44,994 --> 00:28:47,110
No.

542
00:28:47,110 --> 00:28:48,748
I'm scared.

543
00:28:48,748 --> 00:28:52,474
Looks like we've got a little supervisor here.

544
00:28:52,474 --> 00:28:54,517
He's very strict.

545
00:28:54,517 --> 00:28:56,464
Mr. Sun Woo Joo.

546
00:28:56,464 --> 00:28:58,738
No.

547
00:28:58,738 --> 00:29:00,815
By the way, what's this?

548
00:29:00,815 --> 00:29:02,650
Some mail came for you.

549
00:29:02,650 --> 00:29:03,985
From the family court, I think.

550
00:29:03,985 --> 00:29:06,364
The family court?

551
00:29:11,646 --> 00:29:14,360
[Seoul Family Court]
[Appearance Notice]

552
00:29:17,105 --> 00:29:19,298
Yum.

553
00:29:24,964 --> 00:29:27,008
So it says you're not automatically guaranteed

554
00:29:27,008 --> 00:29:29,803
to become Woo Joo's legal guardian?

555
00:29:29,803 --> 00:29:32,013
Yeah.

556
00:29:32,013 --> 00:29:35,095
I thought any family member could,
but that's not how it works.

557
00:29:35,095 --> 00:29:37,712
There are quite a few documents to submit,

558
00:29:37,712 --> 00:29:41,349
and I also have to pass a family court hearing.

559
00:29:42,232 --> 00:29:45,429
So is this the date for the hearing?

560
00:29:45,429 --> 00:29:49,030
No, the guardian interview comes first.

561
00:29:49,030 --> 00:29:51,866
They'll review the documents I submitted

562
00:29:51,866 --> 00:29:55,787
and conduct an in-depth interview.

563
00:29:55,787 --> 00:29:57,441
After that,

564
00:29:57,441 --> 00:30:02,168
they'll decide whether I can become

565
00:30:02,168 --> 00:30:05,134
Woo Joo's legal guardian.

566
00:30:08,911 --> 00:30:11,992
It's more complicated than I thought.

567
00:30:11,992 --> 00:30:13,894
Yeah.

568
00:30:13,894 --> 00:30:17,141
I didn't think much of it before,

569
00:30:17,141 --> 00:30:19,659
but now that I've actually received this,
I'm getting nervous.

570
00:30:19,659 --> 00:30:22,230
And worried.

571
00:30:22,230 --> 00:30:24,274
Come on, worried about what?

572
00:30:24,274 --> 00:30:28,033
If you're not qualified, then who is?

573
00:30:29,153 --> 00:30:30,280
Right?

574
00:30:30,280 --> 00:30:31,739
Yeah.

575
00:30:31,739 --> 00:30:33,783
Don't worry too much.

576
00:30:33,783 --> 00:30:36,019
And there's still plenty of time.

577
00:30:36,019 --> 00:30:39,122
I'll look into some tips

578
00:30:39,122 --> 00:30:41,416
on how to pass it easily.

579
00:30:41,416 --> 00:30:43,668
Okay, thank you.

580
00:30:43,668 --> 00:30:45,197
No need to thank me.

581
00:30:45,197 --> 00:30:47,422
Of course I'd help.

582
00:30:47,422 --> 00:30:49,215
Let's prepare perfectly

583
00:30:49,215 --> 00:30:52,051
and show them that we can raise Woo Joo

584
00:30:52,051 --> 00:30:54,670
better than anyone.

585
00:30:57,209 --> 00:30:59,726
[Minor Guardian Approval Process]

586
00:30:59,726 --> 00:31:03,332
[Let's Take a Look at
the Guardian Appointment Process]

587
00:31:09,889 --> 00:31:12,476
[Requirements and Procedures
to Be Appointed as a Legal Guardian]

588
00:31:14,809 --> 00:31:17,398
[Seoul Family Court]

589
00:31:17,398 --> 00:31:19,465
[Petition for the Appointment of a Guardian]

590
00:31:19,465 --> 00:31:20,937
[Certificate of Family Relations]

591
00:31:26,947 --> 00:31:30,220
[Childcare Schedule]
[Baby Food...]

592
00:31:31,090 --> 00:31:34,156
Woo Joo, you can't do that.

593
00:31:34,156 --> 00:31:36,390
Just a moment.

594
00:31:37,597 --> 00:31:39,390
Hey, Woo Joo.

595
00:31:39,390 --> 00:31:40,642
If you do that,

596
00:31:40,642 --> 00:31:43,061
everything I worked so hard on
is going to get ruined.

597
00:31:43,061 --> 00:31:45,063
So just play a little longer, okay?

598
00:31:45,063 --> 00:31:48,775
How do you plan to manage the ward's assets?

599
00:31:48,775 --> 00:31:50,777
I plan to keep the ward's bank account

600
00:31:50,777 --> 00:31:53,237
completely separate from my personal assets

601
00:31:53,237 --> 00:31:56,566
and manage them accordingly.

602
00:31:56,566 --> 00:31:58,020
Come on.

603
00:31:58,020 --> 00:32:00,411
Okay, just five minutes.

604
00:32:00,411 --> 00:32:02,717
Try this.

605
00:32:03,456 --> 00:32:04,874
That's it, good job.

606
00:32:04,874 --> 00:32:07,293
Sun...

607
00:32:07,293 --> 00:32:08,920
Woo...

608
00:32:08,920 --> 00:32:10,421
Joo.

609
00:32:10,421 --> 00:32:12,229
There we go.

610
00:32:12,229 --> 00:32:14,203
Let's finish this first, then we can play.

611
00:32:14,203 --> 00:32:15,246
Yeah.

612
00:32:15,246 --> 00:32:16,636
Hey,

613
00:32:16,636 --> 00:32:19,097
do you really need to prepare this intensely?

614
00:32:19,097 --> 00:32:20,431
I mean, you're Woo Joo's aunt.

615
00:32:20,431 --> 00:32:21,418
Of course you'll get approved.

616
00:32:21,418 --> 00:32:24,686
Still, I want to be recognized
as a perfect guardian.

617
00:32:24,686 --> 00:32:27,512
Alright, next question.

618
00:32:31,173 --> 00:32:32,587
You got a text.

619
00:32:33,222 --> 00:32:35,768
It's from "My Safe Place."

620
00:32:40,144 --> 00:32:41,995
Hey.

621
00:32:41,995 --> 00:32:44,580
Is that your in-law?

622
00:32:44,580 --> 00:32:46,791
Yeah.

623
00:32:46,791 --> 00:32:48,584
That just gave me chills.

624
00:32:48,584 --> 00:32:50,837
After all the fighting you two used to do,

625
00:32:50,837 --> 00:32:53,131
now it's "my house?"

626
00:32:53,131 --> 00:32:56,634
Back then,
we didn't really know each other yet.

627
00:32:56,634 --> 00:32:57,734
Like...

628
00:32:57,734 --> 00:33:01,185
we were still figuring things out.

629
00:33:01,185 --> 00:33:04,267
You've really fallen for him.

630
00:33:04,267 --> 00:33:08,062
Well, actually I saw it coming.

631
00:33:08,062 --> 00:33:10,873
I'm glad you realized your feelings

632
00:33:10,873 --> 00:33:12,483
before it was too late.

633
00:33:12,483 --> 00:33:13,568
So?

634
00:33:13,568 --> 00:33:15,737
Happy now that you have a boyfriend?

635
00:33:15,737 --> 00:33:17,321
I'm so happy.

636
00:33:17,321 --> 00:33:19,198
I just want to go home as soon as possible,

637
00:33:19,198 --> 00:33:22,160
and even when I'm exhausted,
just thinking about home

638
00:33:22,160 --> 00:33:26,039
gives me this burst of energy.

639
00:33:26,039 --> 00:33:28,124
Geez, I shouldn't have asked.

640
00:33:28,124 --> 00:33:29,417
Well,

641
00:33:29,417 --> 00:33:31,419
seeing how you moved back in together
right after you started dating,

642
00:33:31,419 --> 00:33:32,990
You two really click, huh?

643
00:33:32,990 --> 00:33:36,078
Yeah. We work great together.

644
00:33:36,758 --> 00:33:38,122
But...

645
00:33:38,122 --> 00:33:40,053
there's one thing we don't agree on.

646
00:33:40,053 --> 00:33:42,013
What's that?

647
00:33:42,013 --> 00:33:45,641
We have pretty different ideas about parenting.

648
00:33:45,641 --> 00:33:48,436
Come here. You need to finish getting dressed.

649
00:33:48,436 --> 00:33:50,841
He said he doesn't want to.
Just let him do it later.

650
00:33:50,841 --> 00:33:51,530
No.

651
00:33:51,530 --> 00:33:53,524
It's getting cold. He'll catch a cold.

652
00:33:53,524 --> 00:33:54,901
Sun Woo Joo, come here.

653
00:33:54,901 --> 00:33:57,570
If he's cold, he'll put it on himself.

654
00:33:57,570 --> 00:33:59,155
Just let him do what he wants.

655
00:33:59,155 --> 00:34:00,698
The teacher said

656
00:34:00,698 --> 00:34:04,985
it's better to clearly say no
when something isn't allowed.

657
00:34:04,985 --> 00:34:06,357
You don't even know what I'm talking about.

658
00:34:06,357 --> 00:34:08,225
Come here, Sun Woo Joo.

659
00:34:08,225 --> 00:34:09,290
No?

660
00:34:09,290 --> 00:34:10,500
No.

661
00:34:10,500 --> 00:34:12,531
You need to wear it. You'll get cold.

662
00:34:12,531 --> 00:34:14,337
- Should we not wear it then?
- Yeah.

663
00:34:14,337 --> 00:34:16,477
Yeah?

664
00:34:19,383 --> 00:34:20,535
Here.

665
00:34:20,535 --> 00:34:22,762
Come here.

666
00:34:22,762 --> 00:34:24,402
It's nine. Time for bed.

667
00:34:24,402 --> 00:34:25,441
No.

668
00:34:25,441 --> 00:34:27,308
It's nine o'clock.

669
00:34:27,308 --> 00:34:28,684
Close your eyes.

670
00:34:28,684 --> 00:34:29,964
You're putting him to bed already?

671
00:34:29,964 --> 00:34:31,674
I barely got to play with him today.

672
00:34:31,674 --> 00:34:33,981
It's already nine. Bedtime.

673
00:34:33,981 --> 00:34:35,141
Play with him tomorrow.

674
00:34:35,141 --> 00:34:37,485
Kids can't go to bed
at the exact same time every day.

675
00:34:37,485 --> 00:34:39,237
Sometimes they stay up later.

676
00:34:39,237 --> 00:34:40,238
No.

677
00:34:40,238 --> 00:34:42,657
Bedtime has to be consistent.

678
00:34:42,657 --> 00:34:44,325
A regular routine

679
00:34:44,325 --> 00:34:46,619
helps with a child's emotional stability.

680
00:34:46,619 --> 00:34:48,241
One day won't hurt.

681
00:34:48,241 --> 00:34:50,581
You just have to be flexible.

682
00:34:50,581 --> 00:34:53,092
And look how energetic he is.

683
00:34:53,092 --> 00:34:54,377
Right, Woo Joo?

684
00:34:54,377 --> 00:34:56,045
Want to play a little longer with me?

685
00:34:56,045 --> 00:34:57,408
Come here.

686
00:34:57,408 --> 00:34:59,245
Hey, I said no.

687
00:35:00,675 --> 00:35:03,735
- Want to play with me?
- Yeah.

688
00:35:14,012 --> 00:35:16,791
See?

689
00:35:16,791 --> 00:35:19,710
That's why we need a consistent routine.

690
00:35:19,710 --> 00:35:21,630
I'm a lion.

691
00:35:23,219 --> 00:35:25,449
I just...

692
00:35:25,449 --> 00:35:28,411
I just thought he'd play for a bit

693
00:35:28,411 --> 00:35:31,111
and then stop.

694
00:35:34,493 --> 00:35:35,904
I don't know.

695
00:35:35,904 --> 00:35:38,451
You deal with him.

696
00:35:53,973 --> 00:35:56,980
He finally fell asleep.

697
00:35:58,399 --> 00:35:59,567
You should lie down too.

698
00:35:59,567 --> 00:36:02,338
I'll put you to sleep.

699
00:36:02,338 --> 00:36:05,073
I'm not a kid.

700
00:36:15,099 --> 00:36:17,425
Close your eyes.

701
00:36:18,211 --> 00:36:23,181
♪ Hush, little Hyun Jin, don't say a word ♪

702
00:36:28,304 --> 00:36:31,515
You look like Woo Joo.

703
00:36:31,515 --> 00:36:33,928
Really?

704
00:36:33,928 --> 00:36:35,436
Yeah.

705
00:36:35,436 --> 00:36:37,480
Especially your eyes.

706
00:36:37,480 --> 00:36:42,002
Even the way they sparkle.

707
00:36:43,110 --> 00:36:45,988
Come to think of it,

708
00:36:45,988 --> 00:36:51,000
Woo Joo might've gotten your sharp nose too.

709
00:36:54,580 --> 00:36:56,610
And we share something too.

710
00:36:56,610 --> 00:36:58,404
- We do?
- Yes.

711
00:36:58,404 --> 00:37:01,337
Where?

712
00:37:01,337 --> 00:37:03,798
Dimples.

713
00:37:03,798 --> 00:37:06,717
You're right.

714
00:37:06,717 --> 00:37:10,438
Maybe that's because we're family.

715
00:37:14,433 --> 00:37:16,936
I like that.

716
00:37:16,936 --> 00:37:20,109
Being family with you.

717
00:37:26,195 --> 00:37:30,324
Want to go on a trip this weekend?

718
00:37:30,324 --> 00:37:31,993
A trip?

719
00:37:31,993 --> 00:37:33,661
Yeah.

720
00:37:33,661 --> 00:37:36,747
Woo Joo's been full of energy lately.

721
00:37:36,747 --> 00:37:38,960
Maybe we could go somewhere,

722
00:37:38,960 --> 00:37:41,919
even just a day trip.

723
00:37:41,919 --> 00:37:45,798
We didn't really get to enjoy
that camping trip last time.

724
00:37:45,798 --> 00:37:48,898
And we could make it a date too.

725
00:37:50,303 --> 00:37:51,359
Sounds good.

726
00:37:51,359 --> 00:37:52,972
Then look forward to it.

727
00:37:52,972 --> 00:37:57,458
I'll make the perfect plan.

728
00:38:10,935 --> 00:38:13,969
What's wrong with this?

729
00:38:16,120 --> 00:38:17,538
- Huh?
- What?

730
00:38:17,538 --> 00:38:19,040
It turned off.

731
00:38:19,040 --> 00:38:21,417
Geez...

732
00:38:21,417 --> 00:38:25,046
How did Ui Jun even use this thing?

733
00:38:25,046 --> 00:38:26,881
I'll check the directions on my phone.

734
00:38:26,881 --> 00:38:28,274
You just focus on driving.

735
00:38:28,274 --> 00:38:30,394
Thanks.

736
00:38:32,428 --> 00:38:33,846
So which way do we go now?

737
00:38:33,846 --> 00:38:35,905
Well...

738
00:38:35,905 --> 00:38:37,224
- Now.
- Now?

739
00:38:37,224 --> 00:38:39,651
What?

740
00:38:40,505 --> 00:38:41,548
- Woo Joo.
- You okay?

741
00:38:41,548 --> 00:38:44,832
I told you not to hit things like that.

742
00:38:44,832 --> 00:38:46,634
- So which way do we go?
- Well...

743
00:38:46,634 --> 00:38:49,362
Are we just circling around?

744
00:38:49,362 --> 00:38:51,113
I think I'm getting carsick.

745
00:38:51,113 --> 00:38:52,173
Left.

746
00:38:52,173 --> 00:38:54,186
Left?

747
00:38:54,186 --> 00:38:57,441
Please take the road on the right.

748
00:38:58,496 --> 00:39:01,165
It says right.

749
00:39:01,165 --> 00:39:02,486
Oh well.

750
00:39:02,486 --> 00:39:04,543
We can just turn around. It's fine.

751
00:39:04,543 --> 00:39:06,796
Yeah, a little drive is nice anyway.

752
00:39:06,796 --> 00:39:08,951
I found a good restaurant on the way.

753
00:39:08,951 --> 00:39:10,758
Let's stop there and eat first.

754
00:39:10,758 --> 00:39:12,343
I heard the food's really good.

755
00:39:12,343 --> 00:39:13,427
Sounds great.

756
00:39:13,427 --> 00:39:15,137
I was getting hungry anyway.

757
00:39:15,137 --> 00:39:17,348
Woo Joo, let's eat first.

758
00:39:17,348 --> 00:39:19,141
Let's get some food.

759
00:39:19,141 --> 00:39:21,734
Let's eat.

760
00:39:29,055 --> 00:39:31,404
[No Entry for Children Under 13]

761
00:39:31,404 --> 00:39:35,074
This is the restaurant you meant?

762
00:39:35,074 --> 00:39:36,450
Sorry.

763
00:39:36,450 --> 00:39:38,035
I didn't notice that.

764
00:39:38,035 --> 00:39:39,412
What should we do?

765
00:39:39,412 --> 00:39:41,817
It's fine. It's not the only good place around.

766
00:39:41,817 --> 00:39:43,649
There seemed to be plenty nearby.

767
00:39:43,649 --> 00:39:47,586
Let's just grab something quick
and go have fun.

768
00:39:47,586 --> 00:39:49,332
Alright then.

769
00:39:49,332 --> 00:39:51,250
- Let's go.
- Let's go, Woo Joo.

770
00:39:51,250 --> 00:39:54,398
[Beopgi Reservoir]

771
00:40:02,059 --> 00:40:03,785
Woo Joo.

772
00:40:03,785 --> 00:40:04,822
Stand over there.

773
00:40:04,822 --> 00:40:06,981
I'll take a picture of you two.

774
00:40:06,981 --> 00:40:10,762
Woo Joo, your uncle's taking a photo.

775
00:40:10,762 --> 00:40:12,035
- So cute.
- Say cheese.

776
00:40:12,035 --> 00:40:14,071
- Cheese!
- That's pretty.

777
00:40:14,071 --> 00:40:15,573
So cute.

778
00:40:15,573 --> 00:40:17,722
Cheese.

779
00:40:19,354 --> 00:40:21,776
Smile.

780
00:40:31,130 --> 00:40:33,466
What?

781
00:40:33,466 --> 00:40:35,551
I'm just happy.

782
00:40:35,551 --> 00:40:39,638
Seeing you, Woo Joo, and me
together like this...

783
00:40:39,638 --> 00:40:41,984
I love it.

784
00:40:43,345 --> 00:40:44,504
But somehow

785
00:40:44,504 --> 00:40:47,271
the photos don't capture what I'm seeing.

786
00:40:47,271 --> 00:40:50,316
Nothing's really going according to plan today.

787
00:40:50,316 --> 00:40:52,026
So what if it isn't?

788
00:40:52,026 --> 00:40:53,986
I'm having a great time.

789
00:40:53,986 --> 00:40:56,619
I'm glad you like it.

790
00:40:57,656 --> 00:41:00,589
How did you even find this place?

791
00:41:01,243 --> 00:41:03,245
I filmed here once before.

792
00:41:03,245 --> 00:41:06,540
It was so beautiful I never forgot it.

793
00:41:06,540 --> 00:41:09,001
I told myself I'd come back here someday

794
00:41:09,001 --> 00:41:11,683
with someone I liked.

795
00:41:11,683 --> 00:41:13,797
So that's why you wanted
to come here right away?

796
00:41:13,797 --> 00:41:15,796
Yeah.

797
00:41:17,593 --> 00:41:20,024
- Woo Joo!
- What's that?

798
00:41:20,024 --> 00:41:21,680
A pinecone.

799
00:41:21,680 --> 00:41:23,307
Did you bring a pinecone?

800
00:41:23,307 --> 00:41:25,008
Thank you.

801
00:41:25,008 --> 00:41:26,210
What's this called again?

802
00:41:26,210 --> 00:41:27,458
Pinecone.

803
00:41:27,458 --> 00:41:28,759
Pinecone.

804
00:41:28,759 --> 00:41:29,800
Hold Auntie's hand.

805
00:41:29,800 --> 00:41:31,802
Give me your hand. Let's go.

806
00:41:31,802 --> 00:41:34,109
Woo Joo, are you having fun?

807
00:41:34,109 --> 00:41:35,945
Want me to push you on the swing?

808
00:41:35,945 --> 00:41:36,932
Should we?

809
00:41:36,932 --> 00:41:40,605
- One, two, three.
- One, two, three!

810
00:41:42,393 --> 00:41:43,689
- One more time?
- One more!

811
00:41:43,689 --> 00:41:47,278
- Come here.
- One, two, three!

812
00:41:49,284 --> 00:41:51,470
Having fun?

813
00:41:55,829 --> 00:41:57,925
Yours is bigger than mine.

814
00:41:57,925 --> 00:42:00,928
Right? Put it here.

815
00:42:00,928 --> 00:42:03,538
You stack them like this.

816
00:42:05,210 --> 00:42:08,382
Good job. Let's stack them again.

817
00:42:09,182 --> 00:42:11,621
Come here.

818
00:42:14,893 --> 00:42:17,222
Woo Joo, play by yourself for a minute,

819
00:42:17,222 --> 00:42:18,529
okay?

820
00:42:18,529 --> 00:42:21,059
Just a second.

821
00:42:21,059 --> 00:42:23,284
Every time we stack the pinecones,

822
00:42:23,284 --> 00:42:25,160
he knocks them down.

823
00:42:25,160 --> 00:42:27,329
He never gets tired.

824
00:42:27,329 --> 00:42:28,914
Yeah.

825
00:42:28,914 --> 00:42:30,357
If I knew he'd love it this much,

826
00:42:30,357 --> 00:42:33,530
I would've brought him out a lot sooner.

827
00:42:33,530 --> 00:42:34,931
I kept saying I was busy

828
00:42:34,931 --> 00:42:38,406
and never really took him on a proper trip.

829
00:42:39,758 --> 00:42:43,324
Thanks for bringing us here.

830
00:42:46,432 --> 00:42:47,683
My sister used to

831
00:42:47,683 --> 00:42:50,725
travel with him all the time.

832
00:42:50,725 --> 00:42:52,688
What are you worried about?

833
00:42:52,688 --> 00:42:54,023
We can just come out like this

834
00:42:54,023 --> 00:42:56,894
whenever we have time.

835
00:43:02,156 --> 00:43:03,407
Do you think

836
00:43:03,407 --> 00:43:06,860
I'll pass the guardian review?

837
00:43:10,000 --> 00:43:12,201
Ta-da!

838
00:43:12,201 --> 00:43:14,126
A four-leaf clover.

839
00:43:14,126 --> 00:43:15,336
Where did you find that?

840
00:43:15,336 --> 00:43:16,920
Over there earlier.

841
00:43:16,920 --> 00:43:18,669
Now that we found this,

842
00:43:18,669 --> 00:43:22,386
you're definitely going to pass.

843
00:43:23,177 --> 00:43:24,539
I've never seen this before.

844
00:43:24,539 --> 00:43:27,378
- Really?
- Yeah.

845
00:43:29,831 --> 00:43:31,518
I just...

846
00:43:31,518 --> 00:43:35,175
suddenly find myself worrying.

847
00:43:35,175 --> 00:43:36,856
Maybe it's because this is the first time

848
00:43:36,856 --> 00:43:40,194
I'll be recognized as Woo Joo's guardian.

849
00:43:40,194 --> 00:43:42,363
I'm just nervous.

850
00:43:42,363 --> 00:43:44,865
There's nothing to be nervous about.

851
00:43:44,865 --> 00:43:49,078
Anyone can see how sincere you are

852
00:43:49,078 --> 00:43:51,958
about Woo Joo.

853
00:43:54,147 --> 00:43:55,207
And

854
00:43:55,207 --> 00:43:56,877
now that we found a four-leaf clover,

855
00:43:56,877 --> 00:43:58,615
I've got a good feeling.

856
00:43:58,615 --> 00:44:00,589
But can I really keep this?

857
00:44:00,589 --> 00:44:02,007
Sure. I already have one.

858
00:44:02,007 --> 00:44:03,801
Really? You have two?

859
00:44:03,801 --> 00:44:06,470
Where? Let me see.

860
00:44:06,470 --> 00:44:09,136
Come closer.

861
00:44:12,017 --> 00:44:14,690
Mine's right here.

862
00:44:15,354 --> 00:44:17,314
What?

863
00:44:17,314 --> 00:44:19,316
Probably

864
00:44:19,316 --> 00:44:22,528
the prettiest four-leaf clover in the world.

865
00:44:22,528 --> 00:44:24,516
- Really?
- Yeah.

866
00:44:24,516 --> 00:44:25,989
Don't change your mind.

867
00:44:25,989 --> 00:44:27,616
I won't.

868
00:44:27,616 --> 00:44:30,442
I couldn't even if I tried.

869
00:44:31,408 --> 00:44:33,497
Don't worry.

870
00:44:33,497 --> 00:44:35,797
Thank you.

871
00:44:36,771 --> 00:44:38,231
- Woo Joo.
- Yeah.

872
00:44:38,231 --> 00:44:41,624
Did you have fun today?

873
00:44:47,365 --> 00:44:49,367
- Did you poop?
- Yeah.

874
00:44:49,367 --> 00:44:51,042
Did he poop? Should we stop at a rest stop?

875
00:44:51,042 --> 00:44:54,831
Yeah, let's pull over and change his diaper.

876
00:44:54,831 --> 00:44:57,250
Okay.

877
00:44:57,250 --> 00:44:59,585
- Let's change your diaper, okay?
- Yeah.

878
00:44:59,585 --> 00:45:00,818
You're so cute.

879
00:45:00,818 --> 00:45:03,684
That's quite a smell.

880
00:45:05,547 --> 00:45:07,953
[Mokryeong Rest Area]

881
00:45:07,953 --> 00:45:10,753
[Restroom]

882
00:45:12,843 --> 00:45:15,103
Let's go.

883
00:45:16,065 --> 00:45:19,439
Should we find Uncle?

884
00:45:19,439 --> 00:45:21,822
- Woo Joo, ready to go?
- Let's go.

885
00:45:21,822 --> 00:45:24,342
Hold my hand.

886
00:45:28,698 --> 00:45:29,699
What?

887
00:45:29,699 --> 00:45:31,951
What's wrong?

888
00:45:31,951 --> 00:45:33,828
Why all of a sudden?

889
00:45:33,828 --> 00:45:35,913
Dinosaur toy.

890
00:45:35,913 --> 00:45:38,291
Dinosaur? Where's his toy?

891
00:45:38,291 --> 00:45:39,840
Oh, maybe we left it inside.

892
00:45:39,840 --> 00:45:41,669
I'll go get it. Wait here.

893
00:45:41,669 --> 00:45:44,338
Woo Joo, Auntie will get it.

894
00:45:44,338 --> 00:45:46,264
You can't eat that. Spit it out.

895
00:45:46,264 --> 00:45:48,436
Good.

896
00:46:07,875 --> 00:46:09,322
Is it not inside?

897
00:46:09,322 --> 00:46:12,283
Did we even bring it out of the car?

898
00:46:12,283 --> 00:46:13,701
Maybe it's in the car.

899
00:46:13,701 --> 00:46:15,019
Wait here. I'll go check.

900
00:46:15,019 --> 00:46:17,447
Hold my hand.

901
00:46:18,644 --> 00:46:20,249
Woo Joo,

902
00:46:20,249 --> 00:46:21,709
Uncle will get it.

903
00:46:21,709 --> 00:46:24,331
Let's wait here, okay?

904
00:46:26,631 --> 00:46:28,549
Isn't that it?

905
00:46:28,549 --> 00:46:30,904
I think that's it.

906
00:46:37,565 --> 00:46:39,448
No...

907
00:46:39,448 --> 00:46:41,639
That's not it.

908
00:46:42,730 --> 00:46:43,940
Woo Joo?

909
00:46:43,940 --> 00:46:45,007
Woo Joo.

910
00:46:45,007 --> 00:46:47,208
Woo Joo?

911
00:46:49,278 --> 00:46:51,877
Where did he go?

912
00:46:52,503 --> 00:46:54,200
Woo Joo.

913
00:46:54,200 --> 00:46:56,503
Woo Joo.

914
00:46:57,537 --> 00:46:59,830
Oh my...

915
00:47:04,126 --> 00:47:07,228
It was in the car.

916
00:47:07,228 --> 00:47:08,548
Where's Woo Joo?

917
00:47:08,548 --> 00:47:10,716
He's gone.

918
00:47:10,716 --> 00:47:12,703
Woo Joo's gone.

919
00:47:12,703 --> 00:47:15,849
What do you mean gone?

920
00:47:16,664 --> 00:47:17,790
Woo Joo...

921
00:47:17,790 --> 00:47:19,150
- Don't worry. We'll find him.
- What do we do?

922
00:47:19,150 --> 00:47:20,309
It's okay.

923
00:47:20,309 --> 00:47:22,980
Come on.

924
00:47:22,980 --> 00:47:24,654
Woo Joo!

925
00:47:24,654 --> 00:47:26,665
Sun Woo Joo!

926
00:47:26,665 --> 00:47:29,242
Have you seen a little boy about this tall?

927
00:47:29,242 --> 00:47:30,068
No.

928
00:47:30,068 --> 00:47:31,737
Sorry.

929
00:47:31,737 --> 00:47:32,552
Woo Joo!

930
00:47:32,552 --> 00:47:34,414
Have you seen a little boy?

931
00:47:34,414 --> 00:47:36,033
Sorry.

932
00:47:36,033 --> 00:47:38,393
Sun Woo Joo!

933
00:47:39,416 --> 00:47:42,081
Excuse me, have you seen a child alone?

934
00:47:42,081 --> 00:47:43,291
Woo Joo...

935
00:47:43,291 --> 00:47:46,504
Woo Joo! Woo Joo!

936
00:47:51,488 --> 00:47:53,175
Woo Joo!

937
00:47:53,175 --> 00:47:55,601
Woo Joo, Uncle's here!

938
00:47:57,065 --> 00:47:59,932
Woo Joo!

939
00:47:59,932 --> 00:48:01,155
Woo Joo.

940
00:48:01,155 --> 00:48:02,719
Woo Joo...

941
00:48:02,719 --> 00:48:04,437
Sorry.

942
00:48:04,437 --> 00:48:07,023
Woo Joo!

943
00:48:09,150 --> 00:48:10,234
Woo Joo!

944
00:48:10,234 --> 00:48:11,360
Tae Hyung.

945
00:48:11,360 --> 00:48:14,207
Did you find him?

946
00:48:14,207 --> 00:48:15,371
What do we do?

947
00:48:15,371 --> 00:48:16,991
If I hadn't let go of his hand...

948
00:48:16,991 --> 00:48:19,035
Hyun Jin, look at me.

949
00:48:19,035 --> 00:48:22,079
He can't have gone far. I'll find him.

950
00:48:22,079 --> 00:48:24,415
Just trust me.

951
00:48:24,415 --> 00:48:25,416
Excuse me.

952
00:48:25,416 --> 00:48:27,715
Why don't you go to the management office

953
00:48:27,715 --> 00:48:29,629
and ask them to make an announcement?

954
00:48:29,629 --> 00:48:32,075
Over there.

955
00:48:37,475 --> 00:48:40,139
It's this boy. He's 22 months old.

956
00:48:40,139 --> 00:48:43,517
He's wearing red sneakers and suspenders.

957
00:48:43,517 --> 00:48:45,568
His name is Sun Woo Joo.

958
00:48:45,568 --> 00:48:48,439
Please help us find him.

959
00:48:48,439 --> 00:48:50,358
We'll make an announcement right away.

960
00:48:50,358 --> 00:48:52,068
Please calm down first.

961
00:48:52,068 --> 00:48:54,834
Please hurry.

962
00:48:56,322 --> 00:48:57,531
It's okay. We'll find him.

963
00:48:57,531 --> 00:49:00,493
Attention please.

964
00:49:00,493 --> 00:49:02,370
We are looking for a child.

965
00:49:02,370 --> 00:49:03,829
- A 22-month-old boy
- Woo Joo...

966
00:49:03,829 --> 00:49:06,429
- wearing red sneakers
- I'll find you.

967
00:49:06,429 --> 00:49:08,751
and suspenders.

968
00:49:08,751 --> 00:49:10,461
If you see the child,

969
00:49:10,461 --> 00:49:12,088
please notify a staff member

970
00:49:12,088 --> 00:49:14,924
or come to the management office
on the first floor.

971
00:49:14,924 --> 00:49:17,218
Attention please once again.

972
00:49:17,218 --> 00:49:19,220
We are looking for a child.

973
00:49:19,220 --> 00:49:20,283
Excuse me,

974
00:49:20,283 --> 00:49:22,682
have you seen a little boy about this tall?

975
00:49:22,682 --> 00:49:24,908
Sorry.

976
00:49:30,160 --> 00:49:32,230
Hello?

977
00:49:33,950 --> 00:49:35,827
- You found him?
- They found him?

978
00:49:35,827 --> 00:49:37,641
Yes, we're on our way now.

979
00:49:37,641 --> 00:49:39,870
Let's go.

980
00:49:42,118 --> 00:49:45,621
Mommy.

981
00:49:45,621 --> 00:49:48,935
- Woo Joo!
- Mommy...

982
00:49:48,935 --> 00:49:51,002
I'm sorry.

983
00:49:51,002 --> 00:49:53,254
It's okay.

984
00:49:53,254 --> 00:49:56,257
He was crying in the parking lot.

985
00:49:56,257 --> 00:49:57,717
You must be his guardian.

986
00:49:57,717 --> 00:49:59,260
Yes, thank you.

987
00:49:59,260 --> 00:50:00,761
Thank you.

988
00:50:00,761 --> 00:50:03,080
Good thing you found him quickly.

989
00:50:03,080 --> 00:50:05,891
Kids this age need constant supervision.

990
00:50:05,891 --> 00:50:09,437
He must've been really scared.
Please comfort him.

991
00:50:09,437 --> 00:50:12,397
- Thank you.
- I'm sorry, dear.

992
00:50:15,825 --> 00:50:17,997
I'm sorry.

993
00:50:19,865 --> 00:50:22,087
Woo Joo...

994
00:50:38,869 --> 00:50:40,259
Drink this and get some sleep.

995
00:50:40,259 --> 00:50:42,912
You were really scared, huh?

996
00:50:48,350 --> 00:50:51,270
He must've been terrified.

997
00:50:51,270 --> 00:50:52,980
All because of me...

998
00:50:52,980 --> 00:50:54,857
Nothing happened.

999
00:50:54,857 --> 00:50:58,069
And we found him pretty quickly.

1000
00:50:58,069 --> 00:50:59,320
From now on,

1001
00:50:59,320 --> 00:51:03,290
we'll just be more careful.

1002
00:51:06,994 --> 00:51:10,374
If I hadn't looked away...

1003
00:51:13,292 --> 00:51:14,835
What's wrong with me?

1004
00:51:14,835 --> 00:51:16,879
Stop.

1005
00:51:16,879 --> 00:51:19,159
Come here.

1006
00:51:21,425 --> 00:51:23,594
Once you start thinking like that,

1007
00:51:23,594 --> 00:51:25,429
there's no end to it.

1008
00:51:25,429 --> 00:51:26,754
For tonight,

1009
00:51:26,754 --> 00:51:28,666
don't think about anything.

1010
00:51:28,666 --> 00:51:31,632
Just get some sleep.

1011
00:51:33,020 --> 00:51:35,439
So tomorrow, you can go in there

1012
00:51:35,439 --> 00:51:37,691
as Woo Joo's strong, reliable guardian.

1013
00:51:37,691 --> 00:51:39,872
Right?

1014
00:51:56,919 --> 00:51:59,588
Why are you changing your mind now?

1015
00:51:59,588 --> 00:52:02,758
You said you'd send it by today.

1016
00:52:02,758 --> 00:52:04,100
If we don't submit
the environmental certification

1017
00:52:04,100 --> 00:52:05,246
by the end of this week,

1018
00:52:05,246 --> 00:52:08,618
the review will take months again.

1019
00:52:09,856 --> 00:52:11,293
[Woo Joo's Guardianship Interview Day]

1020
00:52:15,813 --> 00:52:17,690
Hyun Jin.

1021
00:52:17,690 --> 00:52:18,941
Transfer the call to me.

1022
00:52:18,941 --> 00:52:21,054
You're only working a half day today. Right?

1023
00:52:21,054 --> 00:52:22,583
[Woo Joo's Guardianship Interview Day]

1024
00:52:25,298 --> 00:52:28,803
Thank you. Then I'll leave it to you.

1025
00:52:32,746 --> 00:52:34,373
Hello, I've taken over the call.

1026
00:52:34,373 --> 00:52:37,853
This is Park Yoon Seong,
Manager of Planning Team 3.

1027
00:52:42,889 --> 00:52:45,311
Thank you.

1028
00:52:52,600 --> 00:52:54,025
Why isn't she here yet?

1029
00:52:54,025 --> 00:52:56,322
She's really late.

1030
00:52:57,169 --> 00:52:59,535
Hyun Jin.

1031
00:53:01,942 --> 00:53:03,159
Why are you so late?

1032
00:53:03,159 --> 00:53:05,446
Something suddenly came up at work.

1033
00:53:05,446 --> 00:53:06,906
Did you bring all the documents?

1034
00:53:06,906 --> 00:53:08,572
Yeah.

1035
00:53:08,572 --> 00:53:11,219
I'll go in now.

1036
00:53:18,932 --> 00:53:21,478
Yes, please come in.

1037
00:53:24,555 --> 00:53:27,942
[Interview Room]

1038
00:53:34,308 --> 00:53:37,120
Looks like we've met before.

1039
00:53:37,120 --> 00:53:39,980
You got home safely last time, right?

1040
00:53:39,980 --> 00:53:41,377
Yes.

1041
00:53:41,377 --> 00:53:42,949
I'm sorry I'm late.

1042
00:53:42,949 --> 00:53:46,009
Something urgent came up at work.

1043
00:53:46,009 --> 00:53:47,947
Shall we sit down and talk?

1044
00:53:47,947 --> 00:53:50,051
Yes.

1045
00:53:50,051 --> 00:53:52,851
[Parenting Plan]

1046
00:54:02,670 --> 00:54:04,630
Seems like

1047
00:54:04,630 --> 00:54:06,590
you're quite busy with work.

1048
00:54:06,590 --> 00:54:09,176
What time do you usually get off?

1049
00:54:09,176 --> 00:54:10,995
It depends on the day,

1050
00:54:10,995 --> 00:54:14,181
but if I leave on time, I can get off at six.

1051
00:54:14,181 --> 00:54:15,327
So that means

1052
00:54:15,327 --> 00:54:19,812
there are more days
when you don't leave on time.

1053
00:54:19,812 --> 00:54:20,980
Yes.

1054
00:54:20,980 --> 00:54:24,275
That's why you hired a daycare helper.

1055
00:54:24,275 --> 00:54:25,567
Mrs. Park Ae Ja?

1056
00:54:25,567 --> 00:54:26,944
Yes.

1057
00:54:26,944 --> 00:54:29,446
But she had some personal matters,

1058
00:54:29,446 --> 00:54:31,407
so lately Woo Joo's uncle and I
have been taking turns

1059
00:54:31,407 --> 00:54:34,333
dropping him off and picking him up.

1060
00:54:36,210 --> 00:54:37,506
So depending on the situation,

1061
00:54:37,506 --> 00:54:41,166
the helper sometimes changes?

1062
00:54:41,166 --> 00:54:42,216
Yes.

1063
00:54:42,216 --> 00:54:44,079
Some of our neighbors in the building

1064
00:54:44,079 --> 00:54:47,079
help out occasionally.

1065
00:54:47,804 --> 00:54:50,102
I see.

1066
00:54:55,222 --> 00:54:56,765
Did Woo Joo's uncle

1067
00:54:56,765 --> 00:55:00,795
come with you today?

1068
00:55:06,870 --> 00:55:09,563
Mr. Sun Tae Hyung?

1069
00:55:11,856 --> 00:55:14,243
Please come in.

1070
00:55:14,243 --> 00:55:16,433
Yes.

1071
00:55:18,954 --> 00:55:22,458
So the two of you are
currently raising Woo Joo together?

1072
00:55:22,458 --> 00:55:23,792
Yes.

1073
00:55:23,792 --> 00:55:25,971
Having two caregivers is actually very good

1074
00:55:25,971 --> 00:55:28,297
for a child's emotional development.

1075
00:55:28,297 --> 00:55:30,674
However...

1076
00:55:30,674 --> 00:55:33,719
I see there was some conflict
within the family recently.

1077
00:55:33,719 --> 00:55:36,615
You even went to the police station over it.

1078
00:55:36,615 --> 00:55:40,392
Mr. Sun Tae Hyung's father, Mr. Sun Gyu Tae,

1079
00:55:40,392 --> 00:55:42,936
is recorded here as having
"approached the child for insurance money."

1080
00:55:42,936 --> 00:55:45,172
Is that true?

1081
00:55:46,664 --> 00:55:48,292
Yes.

1082
00:55:48,292 --> 00:55:49,534
But

1083
00:55:49,534 --> 00:55:52,404
we'll make sure that never happens again.

1084
00:55:52,404 --> 00:55:55,032
We've already filed a restraining order.

1085
00:55:55,032 --> 00:55:59,800
Did you think something like this might happen?

1086
00:56:00,829 --> 00:56:02,581
Not exactly, but...

1087
00:56:02,581 --> 00:56:06,531
Mr. Sun Gyu Tae is
a convicted criminal who has served time.

1088
00:56:06,531 --> 00:56:08,295
Is it really possible

1089
00:56:08,295 --> 00:56:09,845
to predict and prepare

1090
00:56:09,845 --> 00:56:12,424
for the actions of someone like that?

1091
00:56:12,424 --> 00:56:14,343
From my perspective,

1092
00:56:14,343 --> 00:56:16,894
there's still a strong possibility
that conflicts will continue.

1093
00:56:16,894 --> 00:56:18,305
Especially,

1094
00:56:18,305 --> 00:56:21,738
if money is involved.

1095
00:56:26,416 --> 00:56:27,815
Investigator,

1096
00:56:27,815 --> 00:56:32,194
it's true we may not be
perfect guardians for Woo Joo.

1097
00:56:32,194 --> 00:56:33,634
We're still new to this,

1098
00:56:33,634 --> 00:56:35,900
and there's a lot we're learning as we go.

1099
00:56:35,900 --> 00:56:38,575
But one thing I can say with certainty

1100
00:56:38,575 --> 00:56:39,952
is that our determination

1101
00:56:39,952 --> 00:56:43,163
to protect Woo Joo and
our sense of responsibility

1102
00:56:43,163 --> 00:56:44,998
will never waver, no matter what happens.

1103
00:56:44,998 --> 00:56:48,948
"New to this and learning as you go?"

1104
00:56:48,948 --> 00:56:50,587
Well...

1105
00:56:50,587 --> 00:56:52,005
A child

1106
00:56:52,005 --> 00:56:56,260
cannot understand
that their guardian is inexperienced.

1107
00:56:56,260 --> 00:56:58,662
A child simply deserves protection

1108
00:56:58,662 --> 00:57:02,588
and a stable environment.

1109
00:57:03,517 --> 00:57:05,192
Recently, the two of you

1110
00:57:05,192 --> 00:57:07,695
almost lost the child, correct?

1111
00:57:07,695 --> 00:57:11,316
Was that also because you were inexperienced?

1112
00:57:11,316 --> 00:57:15,994
How can I be sure this won't happen again?

1113
00:57:31,503 --> 00:57:35,216
I'll get straight to the point.

1114
00:57:36,197 --> 00:57:37,301
After reviewing

1115
00:57:37,301 --> 00:57:39,303
all the circumstances
and the submitted materials,

1116
00:57:39,303 --> 00:57:42,147
at this time,

1117
00:57:43,807 --> 00:57:46,185
the two of you are not considered suitable

1118
00:57:46,185 --> 00:57:49,714
to serve as Woo Joo's guardians.

1119
00:58:41,497 --> 00:58:44,500
They're Woo Joo's aunt and uncle.
How can they be considered unfit?

1120
00:58:44,500 --> 00:58:47,253
No one cares about him more than they do.

1121
00:58:47,253 --> 00:58:48,415
We're his family.

1122
00:58:48,415 --> 00:58:50,339
How can they just take him away like this?

1123
00:58:50,339 --> 00:58:52,636
Is there anything I can do to help?

1124
00:58:52,636 --> 00:58:55,636
Could you please reconsider just once?

1125
00:58:55,636 --> 00:58:57,202
Thank you, Tae Hyung.

1126
00:58:57,202 --> 00:58:59,542
So... there's no problem, right?

1127
00:59:00,516 --> 00:59:02,155
Neglect is also abuse.

1128
00:59:02,155 --> 00:59:05,178
For the child's safety,
we will place him under emergency protection.

1129
00:59:05,178 --> 00:59:06,736
What?
